ovider);\n            assertThat(parser.read()).isEqualTo(PARSER_RESULT);\n        } finally {\n            if (previousValue == null) {\n                provider.remove(key);\n            } else {\n                provider.put(key, previousValue);\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static Provider findBootstrapLoadedProvider() {\n        Provider[] providers = Security.getProviders();\n        for (Provider provider : providers) {\n            if (provider.getClass().getClassLoader() == null) {\n                return provider;\n            }\n        }\n        throw new AssertionError(\"Expected at least one JDK security provider loaded by the bootstrap class loader\");\n    }\n\n    public static final class TestProvider extends Provider {\n        private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n\n        TestProvider() {\n            super(\"X509UtilTestProvider\", \"1\", \"Provider for X509Util dynamic-access tests\");\n            put(\"X509StreamParser.TEST\", TestStreamParserSpi.class.getName());\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static final class TestStreamParserSpi extends X509StreamParserSpi {\n        private InputStream inputStream;\n\n        public TestStreamParserSpi() {\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void engineInit(InputStream in) {\n            inputStream = in;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public Object engineRead() throws StreamParsingException {\n            assertThat(inputStream).isNotNull();\n            return PARSER_RESULT;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public Collection engineReadAll() throws StreamParsingException {\n            assertThat(inputStream).isNotNull();\n            return Collections.singletonList(PARSER_RESULT);\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}
